 A man was killed when he was crushed beneath a large refuse
bin at a business on Fortune Road in City Deep, Johannesburg. The ER24 spokesman Russell Meiring said they ER24 personnel
arrived on the scene at 10am to find the large refuse bin against a large
refuse truck. "A man was found lying trapped under the large
bin," said Meiring. Meiring said the ER24 paramedics assessed the man and found
that he had already succumbed to his injuries. Nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead. "The details surrounding this incident are not yet
known but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations,"
said Meiring. 